<item>
            <title>[SPARK-25901] Barrier mode spawns a bunch of threads that get collected on gc</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-25901</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After a barrier job is terminated (successfully or interrupted), the accompanying thread created with `Timer` in `BarrierTaskContext` shows in a waiting state until gc is called. We should probably have just one thread to schedule all such tasks, since they just log every 60 seconds.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a screen shot of the threads growing with more tasks:&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12946439/12946439_Screen+Shot+2018-10-31+at+11.57.25+AM.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a screen shot of constant number of threads with more tasks:&lt;br/&gt;
